  "title": "Chart Of Accounts",
  "description": "A listing of all accounts used in the general ledger. \r\n\r\nA chart of accounts is a listing of the names of the accounts that a company has identified and made available for recording transactions in its general ledger. (Accounting Coach)\r\n\r\nA Chart of Accounts is the master list of all accounts used by an organization to record financial transactions in its general ledger.\r\nIt defines how financial data is classified, aggregated, and reported under the chosen accounting standards (e.g., GAAP, IFRS).",
